# Design file inspiration

Anything related to **frontend features requiring UI/UX changes** must use the files in **[DESIGN_FILE.html](DESIGN_FILE.html)** (at repo root) as inspiration.

**Rule:** When implementing or changing screens, components, or flows in `apps/web` or `apps/mobile`:

- Use [DESIGN_FILE.html](DESIGN_FILE.html) as the **primary visual and layout reference**.
- Align structure, components, spacing, typography (e.g. Lexend), colors, icons (Material Icons/Symbols), and screen flows with the design.
- Where a prompt or ticket says "Match DESIGN_FILE" or similar, implement that screen to align closely with the corresponding section in DESIGN_FILE.html.
- Replicate the same look and behavior in **both** `apps/web` and `apps/mobile` (see frontend-replication rule).

Reference [app-design-prompt-google-stitch.md](app-design-prompt-google-stitch.md) for additional design context where relevant.
